{
  "stem": "14212.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then every single day, they used to take us to go on the road-- fix the roads.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I especially had no luck to them and every day I was called by them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "At one time-- and this went on so close to three months.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Every morning I had to go to work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They brought us back at night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And one time I was pushing a wheel-- a wheel cart on top of a one board to a machine to turn over the-- the stones for them to break it.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I lost my balance and fell down.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the German hit me and-- in my right side, and I don't hear in my ear until today.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then I decided to go away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And coming home, I told my parents that I decided this is my decision.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "If they want, let's go together but they didn't.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And three other friends of mine-- we're four-- and we started off to go to the side of the Soviet Union, to the part where the Russians were.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Then after a week or so of traveling, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we came about the border-- the new border with the new [INAUDIBLE] and the controlled part of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "While we were approaching the Bug-- it was the River Bug-- four Germans came up on horses, and they caught us four.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They brought us back to the city.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was a Saturday morning, and people going to the shul yet then, they thought that this is the finish.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They went [INAUDIBLE] for us, but somehow we had documents, secure documents from the German authority.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We had a neighbor who became the Burgermeister.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "This is the-- the-- the mayor of the city, Zwolen, who was living next to us.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
